{"title_page": "Taurus Model 85", "text_new": "{{Infobox weapon\n|name=Model 85\n| image= Taurus_Model_85.jpg\n| image_size = 300\n|caption=\n|origin=Brazil\n|type= [[Revolver]]\n<!-- Service history -->\n|service=\n|used_by=See \"Usage\"\n|wars=\n|is_ranged=yes\n|cartridge=[[.38 Special]]\n|action=[[trigger (firearms)#Double action|Double action]] / [[trigger (firearms)#Single action|single action]]\n|width= {{convert|1.346|in|mm|abbr=on}}\n|height= {{convert|4.28|in|mm|abbr=on}}\n|rate=\n|feed=5 shot cylinder\n|sights=fixed front sight\n|range=\n}}\nThe '''Taurus Model 85''' is a small-frame [[revolver]] manufactured by the Brazilian firearm company [[Taurus (manufacturer)|Taurus International]]. In the United States, the guns are marketed for concealed carry and personal protection.<ref>[http://www.taurususa.com/pdf/2014_taurus_catalog.pdf 2014 Taurus USA Product Catalog, p. 7]</ref>\n\n== Specifications ==\nThe Model 85 is available in several configurations. These include blued steel, stainless steel, polymer frame, and \"Ultralite\" variants constructed of aluminum and titanium, with steel lockwork components.\n\nMuch like Smith & Wesson revolvers, Model 85s can come equipped with exposed, \"bobbed\" (850), or shrouded (851) hammers. However, there are a number of significant internal differences between the Taurus 85 and similar Smith & Wesson revolvers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.snubnose.info/docs/M85.htm|title=Taurus Model 85|website=www.snubnose.info}}</ref> Because of these differences, Taurus has been able to keep costs relatively low. However, those same differences can make customization of the Model 85 more expensive.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.grantcunningham.com/blog_files/no_taurus_work.html|title=Why I don't work on Taurus revolvers. - www.GrantCunningham.com|date=3 July 2006|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nThere are numerous cosmetic options, including gold-plated hardware and grips of wood or pearl.  The Model 85 is available with either 2\" or 3\" barrels, is capable of firing +P rated [[.38 Special]] rounds, and utilizes a [[Safety (firearms)#Transfer bar|transfer bar safety]].\n\nModels manufactured after 1997 feature the ''Taurus Security System'', which consists of a keyed, quarter-turn style socket-head screw which can be set to prevent the hammer from pivoting back into the frame, thus rendering the weapon inoperative.\n\nThe Model 85 line has been enlarged to include the Model 856. This model is similar to the Model 85, but adds an additional round in the cylinder to bring the Model 856's capacity to 6 rounds.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gunreports.com/news/handguns/Taurus-Revolver_449-1.html|title=Taurus\u2019 856 Revolver - News Article|website=Gun Tests}}</ref>\n\nThe View, also known as the model 85VTA, was introduced in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.taurususa.com/taurus-press-releases-detail.cfm?newsID=59|title=Taurus International Manufacturing Inc - Press Releases|website=www.taurususa.com}}</ref> It has a 1.41 inch barrel, an aluminum frame and titanium cylinder, and a clear polycarbonate side plate for an unloaded weight of 9.5 ounces.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.taurususa.com/product-details.cfm?id=897&category=Revolver&breadcrumbseries=&search=85|title=Taurus 85VTA Revolver - .38 Special 5 Rounds Silver Finish|website=www.taurususa.com}}</ref><ref>[http://www.taurususa.com/pdf/2014_taurus_catalog.pdf Taurus USA Product Catalog, p. 9]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bxJzWCE5XJ4|title=Taurus 85 View SHOT Show 2014 Preview|first=|last=Kentucky Gun Co|date=11 January 2014|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref> Unlike other models, the View is only rated for standard pressure .38 Special ammunition.\n\nReviews on the 85VTA were mixed. Noted author [[Massad Ayoob]] found the View he shot had accuracy problems and bullets tended to prairie dog and bind the cylinder.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://americanhandgunner.com/one-view-of-the-taurus-view/|title=One View Of The Taurus ViewAmerican Handgunner - American Handgunner|website=americanhandgunner.com}}</ref> Another reviewer did not have those problems when testing the gun.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mousegunaddict.blogspot.com/2014/08/taurus-model-85-view-review-clearly.html|title=Pocket Guns and Gear: Taurus Model 85 View Review - A Clearly Different Revolver|first=Bruce|last=F|date=7 August 2014|publisher=}}</ref> Ultimately, the View was not a commercial success, and was pulled from production in December 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gunsholstersandgear.com/2014/12/26/end-road-taurus-view/|title=End of the Road for Taurus View|date=26 December 2014|publisher=}}</ref> A revised model, the \"No View\" with an aluminum side plate replacing the clear one was introduced in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportsmansguide.com/product/index/taurus-85-no-view-snubnose-revolver-38-special-2850019nv-725327611950-titanium-1-barrel?a=1820075|title=Taurus 85 \"No View\" Snubnose, Revolver, .38 Special+P, 1\" Barrel, 5 Rounds - 644753, Revolver at Sportsman's Guide|website=www.sportsmansguide.com}}</ref>\n\n== Usage ==\n{{Refimprove|section|date=August 2018}}\n\n\nOne primary international user of the Taurus Model 85 revolver is Singapore.<ref>https://www.cmpb.gov.sg/web/portal/cmpb/home/life-in-ns/spf/items-issued</ref>\n\n* {{flag|Singapore}}:\n** [[Singapore Police Force]] (SPF)\n** [[Central Narcotics Bureau]] (CNB)\n** [[Immigration and Checkpoints Authority]] (ICA)\n** [[Internal Security Department (Singapore)|Internal Security Department]] (ISD)\n** [[Singapore Prison Service]] (SPS)\n\nAlong with these listed Singapore Home Team agencies, the revolver is also used by several auxiliary police forces in the country, such as Certis Cisco, AETOS and SATS Security, together with older Smith & Wesson .38-calibre revolvers.\n\n{{clear}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Taurus Model 605]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080913121319/http://www.taurususa.com/products/products-revolvers.cfm Taurus USA - Revolvers]\n{{Taurus}}\n\n[[Category:Taurus revolvers]]\n[[Category:.38 Special firearms]]\n[[Category:Military revolvers]]\n[[Category:Police weapons]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox weapon\n|name=Model 85\n| image= Taurus_Model_85.jpg\n| image_size = 300\n|caption=\n|origin=Brazil\n|type= [[Revolver]]\n<!-- Service history -->\n|service=\n|used_by=See \"Usage\"\n|wars=\n|is_ranged=yes\n|cartridge=[[.38 Special]]\n|action=[[trigger (firearms)#Double action|Double action]] / [[trigger (firearms)#Single action|single action]]\n|width= {{convert|1.346|in|mm|abbr=on}}\n|height= {{convert|4.28|in|mm|abbr=on}}\n|rate=\n|feed=5 shot cylinder\n|sights=fixed front sight\n|range=\n}}\nThe '''Taurus Model 85''' is a small-frame [[revolver]] manufactured by the Brazilian firearm company [[Taurus (manufacturer)|Taurus International]]. In the United States, the guns are marketed for concealed carry and personal protection.<ref>[http://www.taurususa.com/pdf/2014_taurus_catalog.pdf 2014 Taurus USA Product Catalog, p. 7]</ref>\n\n== Specifications ==\nThe Model 85 is available in several configurations. These include blued steel, stainless steel, polymer frame, and \"Ultralite\" variants constructed of aluminum and titanium, with steel lockwork components.\n\nMuch like Smith & Wesson revolvers, Model 85s can come equipped with exposed, \"bobbed\" (850), or shrouded (851) hammers. However, there are a number of significant internal differences between the Taurus 85 and similar Smith & Wesson revolvers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.snubnose.info/docs/M85.htm|title=Taurus Model 85|website=www.snubnose.info}}</ref> Because of these differences, Taurus has been able to keep costs relatively low. However, those same differences can make customization of the Model 85 more expensive.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.grantcunningham.com/blog_files/no_taurus_work.html|title=Why I don't work on Taurus revolvers. - www.GrantCunningham.com|