ad accuracy problems and bullets tended to prairie dog and bind the cylinder.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://americanhandgunner.com/one-view-of-the-taurus-view/|title=One View Of The Taurus ViewAmerican Handgunner - American Handgunner|website=americanhandgunner.com}}</ref> Another reviewer did not have those problems when testing the gun.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mousegunaddict.blogspot.com/2014/08/taurus-model-85-view-review-clearly.html|title=Pocket Guns and Gear: Taurus Model 85 View Review - A Clearly Different Revolver|first=Bruce|last=F|date=7 August 2014|publisher=}}</ref> Ultimately, the View was not a commercial success, and was pulled from production in December 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gunsholstersandgear.com/2014/12/26/end-road-taurus-view/|title=End of the Road for Taurus View|date=26 December 2014|publisher=}}</ref> A revised model, the \"No View\" with an aluminum side plate replacing the clear one was introduced in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportsmansguide.com/product/index/taurus-85-no-view-snubnose-revolver-38-special-2850019nv-725327611950-titanium-1-barrel?a=1820075|title=Taurus 85 \"No View\" Snubnose, Revolver, .38 Special+P, 1\" Barrel, 5 Rounds - 644753, Revolver at Sportsman's Guide|website=www.sportsmansguide.com}}</ref>\n\n== Usage ==\n{{Refimprove|section|date=August 2018}}\n\n\nOne primary international user of the Taurus Model 85 revolver is Singapore.\n\n* {{flag|Singapore}}:\n** [[Singapore Police Force]] (SPF)\n** [[Central Narcotics Bureau]] (CNB)\n** [[Immigration and Checkpoints Authority]] (ICA)\n** [[Internal Security Department (Singapore)|Internal Security Department]] (ISD)\n** [[Singapore Prison Service]] (SPS)\n\nAlong with these listed Singapore Home Team agencies, the revolver is also used by several auxiliary police forces in the country, such as Certis Cisco, AETOS and SATS Security, together with older Smith & Wesson .38-calibre revolvers.\n\n{{clear}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Taurus Model 605]]\n\n==Re